$ A small instance of the pythagorean triples problem, as used in our modref
$ 2025 paper: "Solver Aided Expansion of Loops to Avoid Generate and Test"

language ESSENCE' 1.0

$ Partition the set {1..N} into two classes

letting n be 10

find class : matrix indexed by [int(1..n)] of int(1..2)
 
such that

and([(a**2 + b**2 = c**2 /\ a<=b /\ b<=c) -> or([class[a] != class[b],class[b] != class[c],class[c] != class[a]]) | a: int(1..n), b: int(1..n), c: int(1..n)])
